@startuml
title Custom Analysis for Redaction Review with TwelveLabs
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  ArrowFontColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #05D887
  ParticipantFontColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantFontStyle bold
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #05D887
  ActorFontColor #111111
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F4FFF9
  BorderColor #05D887
  FontColor #111111
}
actor User
participant "Frontend\nAnalyze Panel" as FE
participant "Flask API\nAnalysis Route" as API
participant "TwelveLabs Analyze API\nVideo Understanding" as Analyze
User -> FE: Open video in editor
FE --> User: Show timeline, search lanes,\nand detected targets
User -> FE: Enter custom redaction question\nor select a suggested review prompt
FE -> API: POST /api/analyze-custom\nvideo_id, prompt
API -> API: Validate request and add\nstructured response instruction
API -> Analyze: client.analyze(video_id, enhanced_prompt,\ntemperature=0.2)
note left of Analyze
Model
TwelveLabs Analyze answers the user's
custom redaction review query, such as
sensitive scenes, courtroom discussion and any open ended question
end note
Analyze --> API: analysis result
API --> FE: custom analysis answer
FE --> User: Display redaction relevant response
@enduml